                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="48160" author="pjones" created="Wed, 21 Nov 2012 00:32:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Landed for 2.4&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="47918" author="niu" created="Fri, 16 Nov 2012 05:53:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt; &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/4596&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/4596&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="47916" author="niu" created="Fri, 16 Nov 2012 05:36:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;yes, I&apos;ve get confirm from Li Wei and Yujian. I&apos;m going to make a patch to remove all the FSTYPE in test scripts.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="47915" author="johann" created="Fri, 16 Nov 2012 05:31:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think we should use facet_fstype instead. Li Wei, could you please advise? TIA&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="47913" author="niu" created="Fri, 16 Nov 2012 04:36:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;hmm, looks it was running over zfs osd, why we trying to read /proc/fs../osd-ldiskfs/.../enabled? The $FSTYPE is &apos;ldiskfs&apos; for &apos;zfs&apos; testing?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="47912" author="johann" created="Fri, 16 Nov 2012 04:34:14 +0000"  >&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;c04: error: get_param: /proc/{fs,sys}/{lnet,lustre}/osd-ldiskfs/lustre-OST0000/quota_slave/enabled: Found no match
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;hm, if running with zfs backend, it should search in osd-zfs directory, not osd-ldiskfs. It seems that sanity-quota is using FSTYPE in a couple of places, while i think it should use facet_fstype instead, LiWei, do you confirm?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
